<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-26T15:57:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-26T15:57:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23733: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Frontera</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Blohm</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Frontera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-26T14:00:00-06:57"><hi rend="italic">April 26,
                                            1920—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 27—6:30
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Department’s April 23rd 5 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d149fn8">See
                                    footnote 6, <ref target="#pg_143">p. 143</ref>.</note> American
                                citizens and American interests asking me protection against
                                disorganized ruthless bands revolutionists threatening Frontera.
                                Interruption communications expected every moment. Warship draft of
                                10 feet needed entering river.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Blohm</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>